text: Nails Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Georgia. It is a tributary to the Hudson River. Variant names are "Nail Creek" and "Nealls Creek". ==See also== *Cromer's Mill Covered Bridge ==References== Category:Rivers of Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Bodies of water of Banks County, Georgia Category:Bodies of water of Franklin County, Georgia Category:Bodies of water of Madison County, Georgia
title: Nails Creek
